column1: Timestamp of each PUMA device reading
column2: State of the stove when powered on; depends on the stove type the PUMA device is attached to
column3: Number of cumulative clicks since PuMA installation the fuel pump solenoid makes when the stove turns on
column4: Number of clicks the fuel pump solenoid makes when the stove turns on per time interval
column5: The amount of fuel consumed by the stove
column6: The fuel consumption rate of the stove
column7: Indoor temperature read by the thermistor monitored by the PUMA device
column8: Outdoor temperature interpolated using area temperature data from Snotel
column9: Temperature difference between the indoor and outdoor temperatures

column2: Integer units corresponding to power states; -1 indicates powered off
column3: Number of cumulative clicks; -1 indicates stove powered off
